1
00:03:23,680 --> 00:03:24,920
A man should never

2
00:03:25,440 --> 00:03:26,640
look down on women.

3
00:03:26,720 --> 00:03:29,080
PREVIOUSLY

4
00:03:30,160 --> 00:03:31,000
Petch!

5
00:03:31,080 --> 00:03:31,960
- You killed Joe!
- Joe!

6
00:03:32,040 --> 00:03:33,040
- Dad.
- Petch!

7
00:03:33,120 --> 00:03:34,120
Dad!

8
00:03:34,720 --> 00:03:35,920
Where is Petch, then?

9
00:03:36,520 --> 00:03:38,480
Listen carefully.

10
00:03:39,080 --> 00:03:40,920
<i>He doesn't want anything to do with you.</i>

11
00:03:41,000 --> 00:03:43,960
She changed her mind and wants
to study abroad all of a sudden.

12
00:03:45,000 --> 00:03:45,840
Dao.

13
00:03:46,360 --> 00:03:48,160
- Are you serious?
- Yes.

14
00:03:48,240 --> 00:03:49,520
What are you here for?

15
00:03:52,240 --> 00:03:53,640
I don't care how tough you are.

16
00:03:53,720 --> 00:03:56,040
Right here, I've taken over.

17
00:03:56,120 --> 00:03:57,480
Don't pick on Petch!

18
00:03:58,360 --> 00:03:59,720
Dam?

19
00:04:03,840 --> 00:04:07,760
SAN FRANCISCO, USA

20
00:04:21,040 --> 00:04:23,440
Here. For my brilliant woman.

21
00:04:28,920 --> 00:04:29,840
Thank you.

22
00:04:35,960 --> 00:04:38,760
I followed your parents for work
to San Francisco,

23
00:04:39,280 --> 00:04:41,120
so I came to check up on you.

24
00:04:43,440 --> 00:04:45,160
Why are you here then?

25
00:04:49,560 --> 00:04:53,200
I just need to know

26
00:04:54,280 --> 00:04:56,160
whether you're hiding any man here.

27
00:04:58,040 --> 00:04:59,000
No, I'm not.

28
00:04:59,600 --> 00:05:00,720
Exactly.

29
00:05:01,720 --> 00:05:03,360
Someone like Petch

30
00:05:04,360 --> 00:05:06,880
wouldn't be able to follow you here.

31
00:05:11,880 --> 00:05:12,760
Ake.

32
00:05:14,200 --> 00:05:16,360
That was ages ago.

33
00:05:17,520 --> 00:05:19,360
Insulting him won't do any good.

34
00:05:20,960 --> 00:05:21,920
Dao.

35
00:05:22,640 --> 00:05:23,520
I was just joking.

36
00:05:24,120 --> 00:05:25,040
You know?

37
00:05:26,400 --> 00:05:27,760
Don't be so serious.

38
00:05:29,600 --> 00:05:30,440
Really?

39
00:05:31,040 --> 00:05:35,200
Then I need to let you know that

40
00:05:35,720 --> 00:05:37,000
I won't fall for anyone easily.

41
00:05:38,360 --> 00:05:40,160
Especially

42
00:05:40,920 --> 00:05:42,080
for a man I have never loved.

43
00:05:43,280 --> 00:05:45,840
No matter how long you try,
even if it is 10 years or 20 years,

44
00:05:46,640 --> 00:05:48,120
it's a waste of time.

45
00:05:55,000 --> 00:05:56,600
Just joking, you know?

46
00:05:56,680 --> 00:05:59,520
I was just joking. Don't be serious.

47
00:06:20,600 --> 00:06:22,200
Right! Petch.

48
00:06:22,280 --> 00:06:23,360
Damrong and Berm

49
00:06:23,960 --> 00:06:25,760
were released from the isolation room.

50
00:06:29,840 --> 00:06:31,040
Speaking of the devil.

51
00:06:35,240 --> 00:06:38,160
Can I join you guys?

52
00:06:38,240 --> 00:06:39,280
I'm full.

53
00:06:44,160 --> 00:06:45,520
What is it this time?

54
00:06:46,440 --> 00:06:48,480
What's going on with you two?

55
00:06:49,080 --> 00:06:50,280
I'm fine.

56
00:06:51,480 --> 00:06:52,600
As for Petch,

57
00:06:54,000 --> 00:06:55,720
I don't know what I did to upset him.

58
00:07:02,160 --> 00:07:03,000
Petch.

59
00:07:06,640 --> 00:07:07,480
Petch.

60
00:07:08,080 --> 00:07:08,920
Petch.

61
00:07:09,000 --> 00:07:09,840
Petch!

62
00:07:12,520 --> 00:07:14,720
What's wrong with you?
Say what's on your mind.

63
00:07:14,800 --> 00:07:16,080
How did you get in here?

64
00:07:18,680 --> 00:07:19,520
Drug possession.

65
00:07:21,400 --> 00:07:22,880
When did you ever touch drugs?

66
00:07:23,560 --> 00:07:25,120
You don't have a record.

67
00:07:26,000 --> 00:07:26,920
I…

68
00:07:27,000 --> 00:07:28,120
I just wanted to see you.

69
00:07:28,200 --> 00:07:31,520
You know what?
I almost got shot to death by the police.

70
00:07:32,520 --> 00:07:34,000
You're out of your mind, Dam.

71
00:07:34,680 --> 00:07:35,880
Look, Petch!

72
00:07:36,600 --> 00:07:40,040
Are you not glad at all to see me?

73
00:07:40,120 --> 00:07:42,560
Should I be glad you committed a crime?

74
00:07:42,640 --> 00:07:45,360
Have you completely lost your mind?
Have you?

75
00:07:47,640 --> 00:07:49,600
When Mr. Nop and I came to visit you,

76
00:07:51,120 --> 00:07:53,120
you never came to see us, not once.

77
00:07:54,160 --> 00:07:56,720
I had to get in here.
Wasn't I supposed to do that?

78
00:08:01,360 --> 00:08:02,320
Petch.

79
00:08:02,840 --> 00:08:03,960
What the hell have you done?

80
00:08:04,040 --> 00:08:05,680
I should have asked you that question.

81
00:08:06,360 --> 00:08:07,720
You ruined your life.

82
00:08:08,480 --> 00:08:09,880
Do you want me to appreciate that?

83
00:08:12,560 --> 00:08:13,840
Petch.

84
00:08:13,920 --> 00:08:14,920
Petch.

85
00:08:15,680 --> 00:08:17,480
I've already crushed my dad's soul.

86
00:08:18,520 --> 00:08:20,920
Are you going to crush
Venerable Grandfather's soul too?

87
00:08:25,400 --> 00:08:26,240
I…

88
00:08:27,840 --> 00:08:28,680
I'm sorry.

89
00:08:30,040 --> 00:08:30,880
Don't be.

90
00:08:32,760 --> 00:08:34,000
I'm done with you.

91
00:08:37,400 --> 00:08:38,520
Petch.

92
00:08:41,679 --> 00:08:42,520
Petch.

93
00:08:43,280 --> 00:08:44,240
I…

94
00:08:44,320 --> 00:08:46,160
I will atone for your crime!

95
00:08:46,960 --> 00:08:48,760
Dam!

96
00:08:48,840 --> 00:08:52,880
Dam! What the hell are you doing? Let go!

97
00:08:54,640 --> 00:08:56,080
Look, Dam.

98
00:08:56,160 --> 00:08:57,400
If you're dead,

99
00:08:58,760 --> 00:09:00,000
I won't have any friends left.

100
00:09:05,400 --> 00:09:06,440
Petch.

101
00:09:10,400 --> 00:09:11,920
You've forgiven me, haven't you?

102
00:09:19,720 --> 00:09:20,920
Don't do anything stupid again.

103
00:09:22,960 --> 00:09:24,760
Now, I've got my best friend back.

104
00:09:33,120 --> 00:09:36,320
SAN FRANCISCO, USA

105
00:09:37,720 --> 00:09:38,920
Dao.

106
00:09:39,000 --> 00:09:41,280
Uncle Sompob is expecting to see you.

107
00:09:41,360 --> 00:09:43,640
Please come join our dinner.

108
00:09:43,720 --> 00:09:45,560
You didn't tell me in advance.

109
00:09:46,280 --> 00:09:47,480
I've already made plans.

110
00:09:48,520 --> 00:09:50,800
Dao. Can you postpone it?

111
00:09:50,880 --> 00:09:52,560
He'll be leaving tomorrow.

112
00:09:52,640 --> 00:09:54,600
Please don't turn us down.

113
00:09:55,960 --> 00:09:56,800
Fine.

114
00:09:57,320 --> 00:09:58,440
See you this evening.

115
00:09:58,520 --> 00:09:59,360
Okay.

116
00:09:59,880 --> 00:10:02,440
See you at 7:00 p.m.

117
00:10:02,960 --> 00:10:04,440
At my place.

118
00:10:06,120 --> 00:10:06,960
Okay.

119
00:10:38,480 --> 00:10:40,080
When will Mr. Sompob be here?

120
00:10:41,560 --> 00:10:43,120
Oh, I forgot to tell you.

121
00:10:43,200 --> 00:10:45,760
Uncle Sompob said
that he would be a bit late.

122
00:10:46,360 --> 00:10:49,320
He's in a meeting with a businessman
who wants to invest with us.

123
00:10:49,400 --> 00:10:51,120
But it's already late.

124
00:10:51,720 --> 00:10:54,280
I think I'd better come see him
tomorrow morning.

125
00:10:55,760 --> 00:10:56,920
I don't think so, Dao.

126
00:10:57,640 --> 00:10:59,200
I think you should

127
00:10:59,280 --> 00:11:01,880
enjoy the moonlight
and taste the wine with me.

128
00:11:01,960 --> 00:11:04,720
I would rather not.
I have an assignment to finish.

129
00:11:06,880 --> 00:11:08,160
But I don't want you to leave.

130
00:11:09,880 --> 00:11:11,200
I want to leave now.

131
00:11:11,920 --> 00:11:13,120
I won't allow that.

132
00:11:13,760 --> 00:11:14,960
Let go, Akekaphol.

133
00:11:15,920 --> 00:11:18,160
- Let go, Ake!
- I don't want you to leave.

134
00:11:18,240 --> 00:11:20,000
- I want to!
- I don't want you to.

135
00:11:20,080 --> 00:11:22,280
I…

136
00:11:23,640 --> 00:11:25,120
Aren't you holding me too tight?

137
00:11:26,880 --> 00:11:27,960
Let go of me!

138
00:11:29,040 --> 00:11:29,920
Dao.

139
00:11:30,840 --> 00:11:32,640
Can you hear it?

140
00:11:33,560 --> 00:11:34,760
My heart is beating for you.

141
00:11:35,520 --> 00:11:36,800
Let me go!

142
00:11:39,200 --> 00:11:40,480
Dao.

143
00:11:41,000 --> 00:11:42,240
You've become a woman.

144
00:11:42,840 --> 00:11:44,160
There's no need to play innocent.

145
00:11:44,240 --> 00:11:46,240
- Let me go!
- Dao.

146
00:11:47,080 --> 00:11:49,000
I have loved you for a long time

147
00:11:49,600 --> 00:11:51,320
and I always will.

148
00:11:53,280 --> 00:11:54,160
Ake!

149
00:11:55,320 --> 00:11:56,160
Let go!

150
00:11:59,920 --> 00:12:01,680
Dao!

151
00:12:03,200 --> 00:12:04,240
Ake!

152
00:12:08,640 --> 00:12:09,920
Come on.

153
00:12:17,720 --> 00:12:18,720
Blood.

154
00:12:19,400 --> 00:12:21,440
I'm bleeding, Dao. It hurts.

155
00:12:24,120 --> 00:12:25,040
What?

156
00:12:30,480 --> 00:12:31,880
I've made up my mind, ma'am.

157
00:12:33,240 --> 00:12:35,160
I won't give up my dream

158
00:12:37,200 --> 00:12:38,240
and I'll continue my studies.

159
00:12:42,240 --> 00:12:43,600
That's what I'm talking about.

160
00:12:45,600 --> 00:12:47,920
Can I have two more
application forms, please?

161
00:12:48,720 --> 00:12:50,000
What for?

162
00:12:51,560 --> 00:12:53,080
For my friends.

163
00:12:57,160 --> 00:12:58,160
I see.

164
00:12:59,440 --> 00:13:01,360
Piak and Damrong too?

165
00:13:01,440 --> 00:13:03,520
I'll play drums.

166
00:13:03,600 --> 00:13:05,400
- Drums?
- I'll draw.

167
00:13:06,680 --> 00:13:09,520
Great. This is so cool.

168
00:13:09,600 --> 00:13:11,120
I can continue my studies

169
00:13:11,200 --> 00:13:13,560
and I've got my best friend back.

170
00:13:13,640 --> 00:13:16,040
And I also have a new friend…

171
00:13:16,120 --> 00:13:18,440
- I'm Piak.
- Piak? All right, Piak.

172
00:13:20,120 --> 00:13:21,760
There's still one thing missing.

173
00:13:22,760 --> 00:13:24,240
What is it?

174
00:13:27,800 --> 00:13:30,560
Here. It is music!

175
00:13:30,640 --> 00:13:32,520
There are drums for me!

176
00:13:34,000 --> 00:13:35,560
Hey, the drumsticks!

177
00:13:40,160 --> 00:13:41,280
Still a pro.

178
00:13:42,760 --> 00:13:44,360
Dam.

179
00:13:44,440 --> 00:13:45,840
Want to start a band?

180
00:13:45,920 --> 00:13:47,720
A hundred percent, yes!

181
00:13:47,800 --> 00:13:50,200
You're the lead singer and guitarist.

182
00:13:50,280 --> 00:13:52,240
I'm the drummer.

183
00:13:52,800 --> 00:13:53,720
Wait.

184
00:13:55,000 --> 00:13:56,280
Who's going to play the bass?

185
00:13:58,480 --> 00:13:59,400
Well…

186
00:14:03,640 --> 00:14:05,400
Berm, you like playing the bass?

187
00:14:09,320 --> 00:14:10,560
Not much.

188
00:14:11,320 --> 00:14:12,440
I don't know what else to draw.

189
00:14:13,760 --> 00:14:15,520
I think you might like it.

190
00:14:17,760 --> 00:14:18,640
You think so, ma'am?

191
00:14:21,440 --> 00:14:23,000
If I recall correctly,

192
00:14:24,160 --> 00:14:25,360
I smashed a bass

193
00:14:25,440 --> 00:14:28,400
over the head of the homeowner
whose house I was robbing,

194
00:14:30,400 --> 00:14:32,560
so I ended up being sent
to the Juvenile Training Center.

195
00:14:32,640 --> 00:14:35,120
Seriously, bro?

196
00:14:35,200 --> 00:14:36,920
- Too cruel, bro.
- So cruel.

197
00:14:39,280 --> 00:14:40,360
Should we try that?

198
00:14:41,040 --> 00:14:42,120
- Should we?
- No, bro.

199
00:14:42,200 --> 00:14:43,560
May I be excused to use the restroom?

200
00:14:45,400 --> 00:14:46,800
That guy got out of juvie.

201
00:14:47,440 --> 00:14:48,920
When will it be my turn?

202
00:14:52,840 --> 00:14:54,120
Hello, sir.

203
00:14:54,200 --> 00:14:55,280
Hello.

204
00:14:55,800 --> 00:14:59,720
Thank you for taking Ake to the hospital.

205
00:15:01,480 --> 00:15:02,440
No problem.

206
00:15:06,080 --> 00:15:08,800
You bled a lot. How are you holding up?

207
00:15:11,760 --> 00:15:12,960
I'm good, Dao.

208
00:15:13,960 --> 00:15:14,960
No pain,

209
00:15:15,600 --> 00:15:16,760
no gain.

210
00:15:17,360 --> 00:15:18,200
What?

211
00:15:18,280 --> 00:15:21,360
So you're into pain now?

212
00:15:22,080 --> 00:15:23,600
I was joking.

213
00:15:23,680 --> 00:15:24,840
I just

214
00:15:24,920 --> 00:15:26,400
wanted to make Dao laugh.

215
00:15:27,640 --> 00:15:28,720
Right. Good.

216
00:15:29,240 --> 00:15:31,560
But honestly,

217
00:15:32,160 --> 00:15:35,160
how did you fall
and hurt your head like this?

218
00:15:42,600 --> 00:15:43,440
Excuse me.

219
00:15:44,520 --> 00:15:45,360
Hello?

220
00:15:51,560 --> 00:15:55,480
I didn't tell him what you did to me

221
00:15:56,840 --> 00:15:57,960
because I hoped

222
00:15:58,040 --> 00:16:02,040
those ten stitches on your head
would teach you a lesson.

223
00:16:02,560 --> 00:16:05,480
I'm no longer a kid under your thumb.

224
00:16:07,320 --> 00:16:08,440
All right, Dao.

225
00:16:08,960 --> 00:16:10,400
I know you're not a kid.

226
00:16:11,200 --> 00:16:15,200
These ten stitches will always remind me

227
00:16:15,880 --> 00:16:17,560
not to give up on you.

228
00:16:18,520 --> 00:16:19,600
One day,

229
00:16:20,200 --> 00:16:21,520
you'll love me.

230
00:16:22,800 --> 00:16:23,640
Ake.

231
00:16:24,160 --> 00:16:26,400
I don't care what you think about me.

232
00:16:26,920 --> 00:16:30,800
But let me tell you
that my love for you will never waver.

233
00:16:52,720 --> 00:16:53,920
There you are.

234
00:16:54,000 --> 00:16:56,840
Hey, Petch, Piak. It's time for class.

235
00:16:58,000 --> 00:16:59,840
Okay, I'll catch up with you.

236
00:16:59,920 --> 00:17:00,760
Sure?

237
00:17:00,840 --> 00:17:02,640
Okay. Better come quick.

238
00:17:18,839 --> 00:17:21,160
Piak! Piak, what's wrong?

239
00:17:21,240 --> 00:17:22,480
Headache.

240
00:17:22,560 --> 00:17:24,200
Piak!

241
00:17:24,839 --> 00:17:26,119
Piak! Get up!

242
00:17:27,640 --> 00:17:29,120
Piak, you don't look fine.

243
00:17:29,200 --> 00:17:31,320
Let's go to the nurse's room. Get up.

244
00:17:31,840 --> 00:17:32,840
Come on, Piak.

245
00:17:39,600 --> 00:17:40,800
Did you get everything?

246
00:17:40,880 --> 00:17:42,680
More than enough.

247
00:17:42,760 --> 00:17:45,600
We have paint thinner,
glue, and drug kits.

248
00:17:47,280 --> 00:17:51,560
Good. Put all of those
under Petch's mattress.

249
00:17:51,640 --> 00:17:56,440
We'll inform the teacher
and he'll be accused of doing drugs.

250
00:17:56,520 --> 00:17:57,520
Exactly.

251
00:17:58,200 --> 00:18:00,320
I can't wait to see him get screwed over.

252
00:18:04,160 --> 00:18:05,960
Your blood pressure is too high.

253
00:18:08,200 --> 00:18:10,040
Piak is going to be fine, right?

254
00:18:11,040 --> 00:18:13,040
He might have some headaches.

255
00:18:13,840 --> 00:18:15,520
I'll prepare your meds.

256
00:18:15,600 --> 00:18:16,440
All right, ma'am.

257
00:18:17,320 --> 00:18:20,440
Rest here until you feel better.

258
00:18:21,680 --> 00:18:23,080
Don't worry about him.

259
00:18:24,680 --> 00:18:26,720
Thank you so much for taking him here.

260
00:18:26,800 --> 00:18:28,600
Please take good care of him, ma'am.

261
00:18:28,680 --> 00:18:29,760
Of course.

262
00:18:38,840 --> 00:18:40,960
Clear. Nobody is here.

263
00:18:46,720 --> 00:18:47,800
Follow the plan.

264
00:18:47,880 --> 00:18:48,760
All right.

265
00:18:48,840 --> 00:18:49,760
Come on.

266
00:18:53,600 --> 00:18:55,720
He has one nice mattress.

267
00:18:57,040 --> 00:18:58,400
Get everything ready.

268
00:18:59,320 --> 00:19:01,360
We'll do some decorating here.

269
00:19:01,440 --> 00:19:04,560
Put them under there. Come on.

270
00:19:04,640 --> 00:19:05,520
Wait.

271
00:19:07,000 --> 00:19:09,160
Do those not look new to you?
It will look like a setup.

272
00:19:09,760 --> 00:19:11,640
All right. I'll burn some.

273
00:19:11,720 --> 00:19:13,520
- Let's light it.
- Move away.

274
00:19:15,520 --> 00:19:17,960
Here. It is lit.

275
00:19:19,800 --> 00:19:21,600
Burning right now.

276
00:19:23,320 --> 00:19:26,320
- Shit!
- Ouch!

277
00:19:26,400 --> 00:19:27,600
Shoot!

278
00:19:27,680 --> 00:19:29,200
- Shit!
- Shit!

279
00:19:29,280 --> 00:19:30,960
- Fire!
- Fire!

280
00:19:33,120 --> 00:19:34,280
Shit.

281
00:19:35,040 --> 00:19:36,800
Guys, help me!

282
00:19:37,400 --> 00:19:39,040
Fire! What should we do?

283
00:19:39,120 --> 00:19:40,720
Get back and help me!

284
00:19:40,800 --> 00:19:42,280
Chai! Sert!

285
00:19:43,480 --> 00:19:44,320
Chai! Sert!

286
00:19:44,840 --> 00:19:46,000
Shit.

287
00:19:50,800 --> 00:19:51,680
Help!

288
00:19:51,760 --> 00:19:53,600
Somebody, help me!

289
00:20:00,560 --> 00:20:02,160
Hey! Move!

290
00:20:03,720 --> 00:20:04,880
What the hell?

291
00:20:09,520 --> 00:20:10,800
Somebody, please help!

292
00:20:11,560 --> 00:20:13,480
Berm!

293
00:20:17,360 --> 00:20:19,520
- Help!
- Berm!

294
00:20:21,040 --> 00:20:21,880
Berm!

295
00:20:23,240 --> 00:20:24,480
Somebody, help!

296
00:20:24,560 --> 00:20:25,440
Where are you, Berm?

297
00:20:25,520 --> 00:20:26,760
Help!

298
00:20:28,520 --> 00:20:29,520
Berm.

299
00:20:29,600 --> 00:20:30,800
- Berm.
- Somebody.

300
00:20:30,880 --> 00:20:32,240
Berm.

301
00:20:40,080 --> 00:20:41,960
Berm.

302
00:20:42,880 --> 00:20:43,720
Get up.

303
00:20:46,800 --> 00:20:48,000
Berm!

304
00:20:48,080 --> 00:20:49,320
It hurts.

305
00:20:49,920 --> 00:20:50,960
My leg hurts.

306
00:20:51,480 --> 00:20:52,400
Berm.

307
00:20:54,760 --> 00:20:57,160
I won't let you die here, Berm. Get up.

308
00:20:59,720 --> 00:21:00,600
Get up.

309
00:21:00,680 --> 00:21:02,160
Come on.

310
00:21:03,880 --> 00:21:05,320
Hey! What's with this smoke?

311
00:21:05,920 --> 00:21:07,200
Hey! Fire!

312
00:21:09,200 --> 00:21:10,200
Help us put out the fire!

313
00:21:10,280 --> 00:21:11,920
Put out the fire! Get the water bucket!

314
00:21:12,000 --> 00:21:13,880
Hurry! Inside!

315
00:21:13,960 --> 00:21:15,480
Hurry! Come on in!

316
00:21:15,560 --> 00:21:17,200
Hurry up!

317
00:21:17,280 --> 00:21:18,320
Douse the fire!

318
00:21:18,400 --> 00:21:19,800
Petch!

319
00:21:19,880 --> 00:21:20,720
Dam.

320
00:21:20,800 --> 00:21:22,920
- Berm!
- Help me.

321
00:21:23,440 --> 00:21:25,040
Berm, get down. Come on.

322
00:21:26,760 --> 00:21:28,880
Careful with his leg. Are you okay?

323
00:21:29,600 --> 00:21:30,520
Okay.

324
00:21:31,280 --> 00:21:32,440
You're safe now, Berm.

325
00:21:32,960 --> 00:21:34,000
- Dam.
- Right, let's go.

326
00:21:36,600 --> 00:21:37,960
Did you break your leg?

327
00:21:41,240 --> 00:21:42,280
Scoop the water!

328
00:21:42,360 --> 00:21:43,480
- Scoop with our hands?
- Scoop it?

329
00:21:43,560 --> 00:21:44,560
It hurts.

330
00:21:45,400 --> 00:21:46,240
Careful.

331
00:21:46,320 --> 00:21:47,840
Hurry up, guys!

332
00:21:49,600 --> 00:21:50,680
- Hurry!
- Hurry up!

333
00:21:56,960 --> 00:21:59,920
You're lucky that Petch saved you in time.

334
00:22:00,000 --> 00:22:02,720
Otherwise,
you would have died in the fire.

335
00:22:06,280 --> 00:22:09,040
Anyway, rest until you recover.

336
00:22:09,640 --> 00:22:14,680
Then, we'll talk about your punishment
for committing arson.

337
00:22:16,240 --> 00:22:17,080
Yes, ma'am.

338
00:22:18,320 --> 00:22:19,480
I take the blame for everything.

339
00:22:20,600 --> 00:22:21,760
I'll let you rest now.

340
00:22:21,840 --> 00:22:23,600
I'll see you again tomorrow.

341
00:22:25,480 --> 00:22:26,320
Thank you, ma'am.

342
00:22:39,640 --> 00:22:41,000
Berm.

343
00:22:43,240 --> 00:22:44,760
We came to check up on you.

344
00:22:47,040 --> 00:22:48,800
Are you here to mock a loser like me?

345
00:22:49,800 --> 00:22:51,840
Berm, are you out of your mind?

346
00:22:51,920 --> 00:22:53,720
We don't think of you that way.

347
00:22:53,800 --> 00:22:55,280
Stop trying to be nice!

348
00:22:56,360 --> 00:22:57,960
I'll tell you guys one thing.

349
00:22:58,480 --> 00:23:00,080
I went to your sleeping quarters

350
00:23:00,960 --> 00:23:02,680
because I wanted to frame you
for doing drugs.

351
00:23:03,480 --> 00:23:04,560
Come on!

352
00:23:04,640 --> 00:23:06,720
I lost! Do whatever you want!

353
00:23:07,440 --> 00:23:09,040
I don't like to kick someone
when they're down.

354
00:23:10,080 --> 00:23:11,560
I came to see you as a friend.

355
00:23:11,640 --> 00:23:12,760
You're lying.

356
00:23:14,200 --> 00:23:16,000
There is no such thing as "friend."

357
00:23:17,000 --> 00:23:18,480
People only keep you company

358
00:23:19,280 --> 00:23:20,520
for their own benefit.

359
00:23:21,040 --> 00:23:21,960
Berm.

360
00:23:22,480 --> 00:23:25,360
You're out of your mind.
Petch is trying to be nice to you.

361
00:23:25,960 --> 00:23:27,680
Why do you guys
want to be friends with me?

362
00:23:28,880 --> 00:23:31,400
My parents don't even like me!

363
00:23:32,640 --> 00:23:34,080
They left me with my aunt.

364
00:23:35,760 --> 00:23:36,800
When they were in a good mood,

365
00:23:37,720 --> 00:23:38,880
they'd gently stroke my hair.

366
00:23:39,840 --> 00:23:42,080
When they were in a bad mood,
they'd beat the hell out of me.

367
00:23:42,720 --> 00:23:44,400
And the reason I ended up here

368
00:23:45,080 --> 00:23:47,960
was that my aunt made me her drug runner.

369
00:23:51,200 --> 00:23:52,640
When I was released,

370
00:23:53,480 --> 00:23:54,520
neither my family

371
00:23:55,240 --> 00:23:56,920
nor anyone would take me in!

372
00:23:59,000 --> 00:24:00,680
I decided to be a burglar

373
00:24:01,440 --> 00:24:02,880
so that I could come back here.

374
00:24:05,240 --> 00:24:07,320
You wanted to be in charge here

375
00:24:08,280 --> 00:24:10,040
because you wanted
to feel important, didn't you?

376
00:24:11,320 --> 00:24:12,160
Exactly!

377
00:24:13,680 --> 00:24:15,400
Because it made me

378
00:24:16,880 --> 00:24:18,560
feel seen.

379
00:24:19,080 --> 00:24:20,960
I think there are better ways

380
00:24:22,280 --> 00:24:24,080
to make yourself feel seen.

381
00:24:27,160 --> 00:24:28,720
What else do you want me to do?

382
00:24:29,960 --> 00:24:31,240
What is it?

383
00:24:31,840 --> 00:24:32,840
First,

384
00:24:34,720 --> 00:24:36,360
you should accept our generosity.

385
00:24:40,280 --> 00:24:44,280
I drew you a card,
but Petch wrote a message on it.

386
00:24:55,400 --> 00:24:59,680
FRIENDSHIP IS A ROSE WITHOUT THORNS.

387
00:25:00,280 --> 00:25:01,280
"Friendship

388
00:25:03,080 --> 00:25:04,440
is a rose without thorns."

389
00:25:04,520 --> 00:25:05,480
Exactly.

390
00:25:07,800 --> 00:25:08,840
You'll learn that

391
00:25:10,160 --> 00:25:12,240
on the day that you hit rock bottom,

392
00:25:13,320 --> 00:25:16,880
you still have me, Dam,
and Piak by your side.

393
00:25:17,400 --> 00:25:18,320
That's right.

394
00:25:18,400 --> 00:25:21,960
We never expected anything from you

395
00:25:23,160 --> 00:25:25,000
except to be friends.

396
00:25:44,560 --> 00:25:45,600
Thank you.

397
00:25:47,880 --> 00:25:48,920
I really appreciate that.

398
00:25:54,200 --> 00:25:56,880
The second way to make yourself feel seen

399
00:26:00,200 --> 00:26:01,960
is to do what you love, Berm.

400
00:26:05,440 --> 00:26:06,440
Do what I love?

401
00:26:07,040 --> 00:26:08,480
Ms. Kanya told me that you play the bass.

402
00:26:09,520 --> 00:26:10,360
Don't you?

403
00:26:11,760 --> 00:26:12,840
Do you want to join our band?

404
00:26:14,840 --> 00:26:15,960
We're forming a band.

405
00:26:38,280 --> 00:26:40,400
ANCHANAPHISEK CHILD AND YOUTH
TRAINING CENTER'S STREET MUSIC

406
00:26:40,480 --> 00:26:44,160
<i>Don't be afraid of goodbyes</i>

407
00:26:44,760 --> 00:26:47,040
<i>Don't be afraid of time passing by</i>

408
00:26:47,640 --> 00:26:50,440
<i>That is real love</i>

409
00:26:51,520 --> 00:26:55,440
<i>Don't be afraid of going alone</i>

410
00:26:55,520 --> 00:26:58,320
<i>You'll never be alone</i>

411
00:26:58,400 --> 00:27:01,360
<i>Just want you to know</i>

412
00:27:03,680 --> 00:27:08,480
<i>Out of this endless yearning</i>

413
00:27:09,360 --> 00:27:15,040
<i>Hold on, the wait won't be too long</i>

414
00:27:15,120 --> 00:27:20,280
<i>At the edge of the horizon</i>
<i>Where the fading light remains</i>

415
00:27:21,720 --> 00:27:26,040
<i>We will meet again</i>

416
00:27:27,280 --> 00:27:31,600
<i>Let your heart be your guide</i>

417
00:27:31,680 --> 00:27:37,280
<i>Follow its whisper</i>
<i>To find a like-minded soul</i>

418
00:27:38,480 --> 00:27:41,920
<i>No matter how long it takes</i>

419
00:27:42,920 --> 00:27:45,240
<i>No matter how hard it gets</i>

420
00:27:45,320 --> 00:27:48,480
<i>I just want you to know</i>

421
00:27:50,840 --> 00:27:55,160
<i>Out of this endless yearning</i>

422
00:27:56,360 --> 00:28:01,040
<i>Hold on, the wait won't be too long</i>

423
00:28:01,840 --> 00:28:06,480
<i>At the edge of the horizon</i>
<i>Where the fading light remains</i>

424
00:28:08,360 --> 00:28:12,760
<i>We will meet again</i>

425
00:28:19,360 --> 00:28:21,640
JUVENILE TRAINING CENTER

426
00:28:28,520 --> 00:28:30,040
<i>Time passes so fast.</i>

427
00:28:30,560 --> 00:28:32,240
<i>I'm graduating, Petch.</i>

428
00:28:33,560 --> 00:28:36,080
<i>No matter how much time passes by,</i>

429
00:28:36,760 --> 00:28:39,080
<i>I still think about you every single day.</i>

430
00:28:40,320 --> 00:28:41,280
<i>What about you?</i>

431
00:28:42,120 --> 00:28:43,800
<i>Do I ever cross your mind?</i>

432
00:29:06,720 --> 00:29:07,560
Guys!

433
00:29:08,080 --> 00:29:09,840
I've got good news!

434
00:29:15,240 --> 00:29:16,160
What is it, Piak?

435
00:29:16,240 --> 00:29:19,040
Don't tell us your drawing won again.

436
00:29:19,120 --> 00:29:20,520
No.

437
00:29:20,600 --> 00:29:22,240
This is good news for everyone.

438
00:29:22,320 --> 00:29:25,440
"Good news for everyone." What is it?

439
00:29:25,520 --> 00:29:28,920
I heard that Petch, Damrong, and I…

440
00:29:30,680 --> 00:29:34,000
We have been granted a pardon
and are set to be released soon.

441
00:29:34,080 --> 00:29:35,680
Set to be released?

442
00:29:35,760 --> 00:29:38,240
- This year!
- Set to be released!

443
00:29:38,840 --> 00:29:40,200
- Yes!
- Yes!

444
00:29:40,280 --> 00:29:41,840
Yes!

445
00:29:41,920 --> 00:29:44,040
Yes!

446
00:29:44,120 --> 00:29:44,960
Wait.

447
00:29:45,600 --> 00:29:46,560
- Wait.
- What?

448
00:29:48,360 --> 00:29:49,240
What about Berm?

449
00:29:50,040 --> 00:29:52,160
He will be released next year.

450
00:29:55,160 --> 00:29:56,000
Better than nothing.

451
00:29:56,080 --> 00:29:58,000
See you later outside, gentlemen.

452
00:29:58,880 --> 00:30:00,600
Dam, Petch…

453
00:30:01,520 --> 00:30:03,200
and you, Piak!

454
00:30:03,880 --> 00:30:05,080
Oh, man.

455
00:30:06,320 --> 00:30:10,000
Petch, please don't break up the band.
Wait for me.

456
00:30:10,080 --> 00:30:11,360
Absolutely.

457
00:30:13,720 --> 00:30:15,320
Guys, I have something to show you.

458
00:30:15,400 --> 00:30:16,760
Ta-da!

459
00:30:16,840 --> 00:30:19,200
I drew this for you guys.

460
00:30:19,280 --> 00:30:20,120
Brilliant!

461
00:30:20,720 --> 00:30:21,600
Hey.

462
00:30:22,120 --> 00:30:25,680
Look at us.
As if we're getting on the real stage.

463
00:30:25,760 --> 00:30:26,640
Well done, mate!

464
00:30:26,720 --> 00:30:28,560
- Next year, man.
- Next year for sure.

465
00:30:28,640 --> 00:30:30,640
Listen, if you guys keep on practicing,

466
00:30:30,720 --> 00:30:33,520
I guarantee
that you'll be on the big stage.

467
00:30:34,120 --> 00:30:35,040
"The big stage."

468
00:30:35,120 --> 00:30:37,040
That's exactly what I want to hear.

469
00:30:37,120 --> 00:30:39,840
I'm ride or die for you.

470
00:30:41,120 --> 00:30:43,360
- Guys, I mean it.
- So cool.

471
00:30:43,880 --> 00:30:45,360
And I promise you guys.

472
00:30:45,440 --> 00:30:48,360
If you can make it to the stage,
I won't miss any showcase.

473
00:30:48,440 --> 00:30:50,080
I'll be your number one fan.

474
00:30:50,160 --> 00:30:52,200
I'll buy all your songs online too.

475
00:30:52,280 --> 00:30:53,520
Oh, wow.

476
00:30:53,600 --> 00:30:55,120
I appreciate that, Piak.

477
00:30:56,800 --> 00:30:57,640
Is that cool?

478
00:30:57,720 --> 00:31:00,000
I'll put this on the bulletin board.

479
00:31:00,080 --> 00:31:02,840
It will cheer you guys up.

480
00:31:02,920 --> 00:31:03,760
You go do that.

481
00:31:03,840 --> 00:31:04,880
Okay, see you.

482
00:31:06,560 --> 00:31:07,560
Come on, let's practice.

483
00:31:14,080 --> 00:31:14,920
Check on him!

484
00:31:15,000 --> 00:31:17,560
- Piak!
- Piak!

485
00:31:17,640 --> 00:31:18,520
Piak!

486
00:31:18,600 --> 00:31:21,640
- Piak!
- Piak!

487
00:31:21,720 --> 00:31:22,880
- Piak! What's wrong?
- Piak!

488
00:31:22,960 --> 00:31:24,040
Piak! What's wrong?

489
00:31:24,120 --> 00:31:26,080
- Piak! Wake up!
- Piak, stay with us!

490
00:31:26,160 --> 00:31:29,160
Piak has a follow-up appointment today
to review his results from a month ago.

491
00:31:30,000 --> 00:31:31,600
Is there any hope for him?

492
00:31:32,920 --> 00:31:34,720
I'm afraid I have to be honest with you.

493
00:31:35,320 --> 00:31:38,200
Piak has terminal brain cancer.

494
00:31:41,080 --> 00:31:43,880
The tumor is inoperable.

495
00:31:44,880 --> 00:31:49,160
What we can do is manage the symptoms

496
00:31:49,240 --> 00:31:50,960
so the patient doesn't have
to suffer too much.

497
00:31:52,360 --> 00:31:53,680
Which means…

498
00:31:54,280 --> 00:31:56,160
I'm really sorry.

499
00:31:57,200 --> 00:32:00,800
The patient won't have much time left.

500
00:32:15,080 --> 00:32:15,920
Piak.

501
00:32:16,680 --> 00:32:18,040
Rest a lot, okay?

502
00:32:19,120 --> 00:32:20,400
Don't worry about a single thing.

503
00:32:21,840 --> 00:32:22,680
Yes, ma'am.

504
00:32:25,040 --> 00:32:26,720
I don't want anything…

505
00:32:29,040 --> 00:32:30,600
except…

506
00:32:32,240 --> 00:32:33,920
What do you want?

507
00:32:36,600 --> 00:32:38,040
I want to see…

508
00:32:40,120 --> 00:32:41,040
Petch,

509
00:32:42,560 --> 00:32:43,400
Dam,

510
00:32:44,400 --> 00:32:45,240
and Berm

511
00:32:46,440 --> 00:32:48,000
for the last time.

512
00:32:56,120 --> 00:32:58,480
The three of you will be released soon,

513
00:32:58,560 --> 00:33:01,520
so I made a special request
for you to visit Piak.

514
00:33:01,600 --> 00:33:04,080
Come on. We'd better hurry up.

515
00:33:04,920 --> 00:33:05,760
Chop-chop.

516
00:33:14,920 --> 00:33:15,760
Piak.

517
00:33:24,280 --> 00:33:25,520
There you are.

518
00:33:28,800 --> 00:33:29,640
I'm glad

519
00:33:30,440 --> 00:33:31,560
that you guys came.

520
00:33:32,080 --> 00:33:33,560
What are you saying?

521
00:33:36,800 --> 00:33:37,960
You are so close to freedom, man.

522
00:33:41,720 --> 00:33:42,680
That's right, Piak.

523
00:33:43,400 --> 00:33:44,960
- You'll be fine.
- Berm.

524
00:33:45,040 --> 00:33:47,360
- You'll be fine!
- Berm, calm down.

525
00:33:47,440 --> 00:33:50,280
- Berm, take it easy, man!
- You said you'd be the artist!

526
00:33:50,360 --> 00:33:52,000
- You said you'd see us on stage!
- Enough, Berm!

527
00:33:52,080 --> 00:33:53,760
Quiet, man! Keep it down!

528
00:33:53,840 --> 00:33:55,760
- Berm.
- How can you accept this?

529
00:33:55,840 --> 00:33:58,000
- Your best friend is dying!
- Easy, man.

530
00:33:58,080 --> 00:34:00,280
Berm, calm down.

531
00:34:00,800 --> 00:34:03,680
Deep breath, man.
Take a deep breath. Come on.

532
00:34:04,280 --> 00:34:05,200
Berm.

533
00:34:07,720 --> 00:34:08,679
Berm.

534
00:34:09,560 --> 00:34:11,600
I don't want Piak to worry about us.

535
00:34:14,080 --> 00:34:15,760
Only my body will be gone.

536
00:34:18,159 --> 00:34:19,360
But my heart…

537
00:34:20,040 --> 00:34:21,520
will always be with you guys.

538
00:34:29,120 --> 00:34:30,600
Pencil, please.

539
00:34:46,360 --> 00:34:47,360
This pencil

540
00:34:48,159 --> 00:34:49,840
won't have another chance to draw.

541
00:34:52,719 --> 00:34:55,679
But you can use it to write music.

542
00:35:01,760 --> 00:35:03,960
Please keep it, Petch.

543
00:35:22,840 --> 00:35:24,360
Thank you so much,

544
00:35:24,880 --> 00:35:25,960
Petch.

545
00:35:27,720 --> 00:35:28,800
I'm glad…

546
00:35:30,800 --> 00:35:32,600
to be your friend.

547
00:35:43,800 --> 00:35:45,240
I'm glad

548
00:35:47,360 --> 00:35:48,440
to be your friend as well.

549
00:35:51,920 --> 00:35:53,440
Life is short.

550
00:35:55,840 --> 00:35:57,280
You'd better…

551
00:35:59,400 --> 00:36:00,320
follow your dream.

552
00:36:01,160 --> 00:36:02,280
Make it come true.

553
00:36:25,160 --> 00:36:26,920
Piak. Piak!

554
00:36:27,760 --> 00:36:29,640
- Piak!
- Piak!

555
00:36:31,000 --> 00:36:32,360
- Petch, Piak is gone!
- Piak!

556
00:36:32,440 --> 00:36:34,320
- Piak!
- Piak!

557
00:36:35,440 --> 00:36:37,600
- Piak!
- Piak!

558
00:36:37,680 --> 00:36:39,040
- Piak!
- Piak!

559
00:36:39,120 --> 00:36:41,080
Piak!

560
00:36:41,920 --> 00:36:43,160
Piak!

561
00:36:43,240 --> 00:36:44,400
Wake up, Piak!

562
00:37:17,120 --> 00:37:21,240
<i>Don't be afraid of goodbyes</i>

563
00:37:21,320 --> 00:37:23,840
<i>Don't be afraid of time passing by</i>

564
00:37:24,360 --> 00:37:27,600
<i>That is real love</i>

565
00:37:28,200 --> 00:37:31,560
<i>Don't be afraid of going alone</i>

566
00:37:32,400 --> 00:37:35,120
<i>You'll never be alone</i>

567
00:37:35,200 --> 00:37:38,120
<i>Just want you to know</i>

568
00:37:40,400 --> 00:37:45,840
<i>Out of this endless yearning</i>

569
00:37:45,920 --> 00:37:51,360
<i>Hold on, the wait won't be too long</i>

570
00:37:51,440 --> 00:37:58,240
<i>At the edge of the horizon</i>
<i>Where the fading light remains</i>

571
00:37:58,320 --> 00:38:02,520
<i>We will meet again</i>

572
00:38:02,600 --> 00:38:04,600
FRIENDSHIP IS A ROSE WITHOUT THORNS.

573
00:38:04,680 --> 00:38:08,280
<i>Let your heart be your guide</i>

574
00:38:08,360 --> 00:38:13,800
<i>Follow its whisper</i>
<i>To find a like-minded soul</i>

575
00:38:15,240 --> 00:38:19,360
<i>No matter how long it takes</i>

576
00:38:19,440 --> 00:38:21,960
<i>No matter how hard it gets</i>

577
00:38:22,040 --> 00:38:25,600
<i>I just want you to know</i>

578
00:38:27,600 --> 00:38:32,400
<i>Out of this endless yearning</i>

579
00:38:33,160 --> 00:38:37,960
<i>Hold on, the wait won't be too long</i>

580
00:38:38,560 --> 00:38:43,600
<i>At the edge of the horizon</i>
<i>Where the fading light remains</i>

581
00:38:44,880 --> 00:38:49,960
<i>We will meet again</i>

582
00:39:26,120 --> 00:39:27,600
Man.

583
00:39:28,600 --> 00:39:30,120
I miss Piak.

584
00:39:32,200 --> 00:39:33,920
Piak taught me

585
00:39:34,560 --> 00:39:35,640
that it's okay to feel down,

586
00:39:36,520 --> 00:39:37,680
but we must always get back up.

587
00:39:39,120 --> 00:39:40,960
No matter what happens,

588
00:39:42,440 --> 00:39:43,600
let's not give up on our dreams.

589
00:39:47,600 --> 00:39:50,240
If only Piak's spirit could hear us.

590
00:39:51,280 --> 00:39:54,280
He would probably be happy

591
00:39:55,120 --> 00:39:57,240
to see us being released.

592
00:40:07,200 --> 00:40:08,280
Come on.

593
00:40:11,280 --> 00:40:12,920
It's time to chase our dreams.

594
00:40:43,320 --> 00:40:44,160
Duean.

595
00:40:46,200 --> 00:40:47,880
I tidied up Petch's room.

596
00:40:48,400 --> 00:40:49,720
I hope he likes it.

597
00:40:52,240 --> 00:40:54,280
Petch will be out soon.

598
00:40:55,240 --> 00:40:56,840
I'll take our son home.

599
00:41:09,320 --> 00:41:10,280
Thank you, ma'am.

600
00:41:10,360 --> 00:41:12,480
You've always been kind to both of us.

601
00:41:12,560 --> 00:41:14,080
Thank you, ma'am.

602
00:41:14,160 --> 00:41:16,560
I wish you two the best.

603
00:41:16,640 --> 00:41:20,080
May you apply this knowledge
and turn it into lasting success.

604
00:41:20,920 --> 00:41:21,760
Understood.

605
00:41:23,760 --> 00:41:25,960
We will never forget this place,

606
00:41:27,000 --> 00:41:28,360
but we won't be back again.

607
00:41:29,680 --> 00:41:31,280
Goodbye for now, ma'am.

608
00:41:31,360 --> 00:41:33,360
We'll see you later outside.

609
00:41:33,880 --> 00:41:35,000
All right.

610
00:41:35,080 --> 00:41:36,960
You'd better not be impulsive outside.

611
00:41:37,040 --> 00:41:38,800
Don't repeat your mistake, Damrong.

612
00:41:38,880 --> 00:41:42,200
This is the new Damrong.
He won't be impulsive for sure.

613
00:41:42,280 --> 00:41:43,520
Are you sure?

614
00:41:43,600 --> 00:41:44,560
Of course, man!

615
00:41:44,640 --> 00:41:46,080
Petch! Dam!

616
00:41:52,800 --> 00:41:55,120
I came to see you guys off.
Don't forget me, okay?

617
00:41:55,720 --> 00:41:56,880
We won't.

618
00:41:57,640 --> 00:41:59,040
Always in our hearts, man.

619
00:42:01,440 --> 00:42:02,680
Wait for me.

620
00:42:03,400 --> 00:42:04,240
Promise?

621
00:42:09,360 --> 00:42:10,600
Once you're out,

622
00:42:11,120 --> 00:42:12,640
we'll get the band back together.

623
00:42:13,920 --> 00:42:16,640
We are men of our word.

624
00:42:16,720 --> 00:42:18,040
Sure thing.

625
00:42:21,440 --> 00:42:23,560
Okay. Thank you, ma'am.

626
00:42:24,280 --> 00:42:25,720
- Thank you.
- Good luck.

627
00:42:26,240 --> 00:42:27,920
- See you, Berm.
- See you outside, man.

628
00:42:28,000 --> 00:42:29,440
- Let's go, Dam.
- Should I walk backwards?

629
00:42:30,040 --> 00:42:30,960
What?

630
00:42:31,040 --> 00:42:32,760
You've already forgotten your steps.

631
00:42:33,280 --> 00:42:34,400
Come on.

632
00:42:54,280 --> 00:42:56,520
TAXI SERVICE

633
00:43:02,360 --> 00:43:05,520
TAXI SERVICE

634
00:43:06,760 --> 00:43:07,960
Oh, there's a scratch!

635
00:43:08,480 --> 00:43:09,600
Damn.

636
00:43:12,160 --> 00:43:13,440
Call your insurance, please.

637
00:43:13,520 --> 00:43:15,720
No need. I won't charge you, young man.

638
00:43:15,800 --> 00:43:17,240
But I bumped into you.

639
00:43:17,760 --> 00:43:20,360
That's okay.
Get back on the road, young man.

640
00:43:20,960 --> 00:43:22,400
- Really?
- Yes.

641
00:43:22,480 --> 00:43:25,120
I'm on my way to pick up my son.
It's okay.

642
00:43:27,960 --> 00:43:29,040
What?

643
00:43:29,720 --> 00:43:31,040
Is this really happening?

644
00:43:38,160 --> 00:43:39,960
Palms up or down.

645
00:43:41,000 --> 00:43:42,720
Come here.

646
00:43:45,240 --> 00:43:46,880
Get back in your line.

647
00:43:48,280 --> 00:43:49,720
Here they are.

648
00:43:49,800 --> 00:43:51,360
The delinquents.

649
00:43:51,440 --> 00:43:53,200
- Get inside, kids.
- Get away from them.

650
00:43:53,280 --> 00:43:54,560
- Come on.
- Hurry.

651
00:43:54,640 --> 00:43:56,840
Guys. I haven't done anything.

652
00:43:56,920 --> 00:43:59,600
Dam.

653
00:44:01,200 --> 00:44:03,600
Petch, they're insulting us.

654
00:44:05,400 --> 00:44:06,480
Let's get inside.

655
00:44:07,720 --> 00:44:08,760
Come on.

656
00:44:10,320 --> 00:44:13,840
Let go of me! How could you stand
being insulted like that?

657
00:44:14,440 --> 00:44:15,560
How could you?

658
00:44:16,320 --> 00:44:17,440
Where is the new Dam?

659
00:44:17,960 --> 00:44:19,240
The new Dam that won't be impulsive?

660
00:44:20,280 --> 00:44:22,080
Don't prove Ms. Kanya wrong, man.

661
00:44:22,600 --> 00:44:24,760
Those people only talk about the past.

662
00:44:25,760 --> 00:44:27,040
Who would want to be good?

663
00:44:27,120 --> 00:44:28,440
Dam!

664
00:44:28,520 --> 00:44:31,040
Just be good for yourself.

665
00:44:31,760 --> 00:44:33,400
Be impulsive again

666
00:44:34,360 --> 00:44:35,800
and you'll end up in prison.

667
00:44:36,880 --> 00:44:38,040
Let me tell you this.

668
00:44:39,000 --> 00:44:42,120
Those people won't give a damn
about your feelings.

669
00:44:45,000 --> 00:44:45,840
Fine.

670
00:44:46,960 --> 00:44:48,160
I was stupid.

671
00:44:50,880 --> 00:44:53,360
Why is your house so quiet?

672
00:44:53,960 --> 00:44:56,280
Maybe your dad
is driving the taxi right now.

673
00:44:57,920 --> 00:44:58,760
That's good.

674
00:45:00,160 --> 00:45:01,640
What? Petch?

675
00:45:03,440 --> 00:45:05,480
You didn't come here to see your dad?

676
00:45:11,480 --> 00:45:13,040
I just want to grab something.

677
00:45:13,120 --> 00:45:14,280
What?

678
00:45:19,200 --> 00:45:20,040
Come in.

679
00:45:24,760 --> 00:45:26,320
Petch already went out?

680
00:45:26,400 --> 00:45:28,960
Yes. I thought he made plans with you.

681
00:45:31,120 --> 00:45:33,040
I just came as informed in the letter.

682
00:45:33,560 --> 00:45:35,360
Petch never told me a thing.

683
00:45:36,160 --> 00:45:39,480
My son never tells me anything.

684
00:45:40,120 --> 00:45:43,120
Petch probably doesn't want
to bother your working hours.

685
00:45:43,200 --> 00:45:45,040
He must be at home by now.

686
00:45:46,680 --> 00:45:47,800
Right.

687
00:45:52,360 --> 00:45:53,840
Thank you.

688
00:46:00,080 --> 00:46:03,560
Oh, wow. Your bedroom is spotless.

689
00:46:04,080 --> 00:46:05,160
New pillowcases.

690
00:46:05,680 --> 00:46:08,080
New blanket and bedsheet.

691
00:46:20,240 --> 00:46:21,920
Petch, I think

692
00:46:22,760 --> 00:46:24,640
your dad would be happy to see you.

693
00:46:44,480 --> 00:46:45,400
Hey.

694
00:46:46,080 --> 00:46:47,200
Apart from the money,

695
00:46:47,720 --> 00:46:49,480
is that what you came for?

696
00:46:53,160 --> 00:46:55,520
This is the most precious item in my life.

697
00:46:56,760 --> 00:46:58,720
Petch, tell me the truth.

698
00:46:59,960 --> 00:47:01,360
Are you really leaving this place?

699
00:47:04,520 --> 00:47:06,000
I made a promise to myself.

700
00:47:07,000 --> 00:47:08,840
If I don't succeed,

701
00:47:10,240 --> 00:47:11,960
I won't face my dad ever again.

702
00:47:20,680 --> 00:47:21,640
Duean.

703
00:47:22,760 --> 00:47:24,200
Please guide our son's heart.

704
00:47:24,960 --> 00:47:26,560
Don't let him do what I think he would.

705
00:47:27,760 --> 00:47:28,720
Please, sweetheart.

706
00:48:20,520 --> 00:48:21,360
<i>Dad,</i>

707
00:48:22,520 --> 00:48:24,320
<i>I don't want to shame you.</i>

708
00:48:25,520 --> 00:48:27,440
<i>If I can't prove myself,</i>

709
00:48:28,720 --> 00:48:30,520
<i>I won't have any pride left to face you.</i>

710
00:48:31,680 --> 00:48:32,880
<i>It won't be long</i>

711
00:48:34,360 --> 00:48:35,520
<i>before we meet again.</i>

712
00:48:37,240 --> 00:48:38,160
<i>Petch.</i>

713
00:48:42,840 --> 00:48:43,680
Oh, boy.

714
00:48:45,080 --> 00:48:46,840
Why are you being like this?

715
00:49:07,160 --> 00:49:08,800
Dao, sweetheart.

716
00:49:09,400 --> 00:49:10,320
Dear.

717
00:49:12,760 --> 00:49:14,000
Look at you.

718
00:49:14,080 --> 00:49:16,320
It has only been four or five years.

719
00:49:16,400 --> 00:49:19,000
You're all grown up.
I almost didn't recognize you.

720
00:49:20,000 --> 00:49:21,520
Did the long travel exhaust you?

721
00:49:22,120 --> 00:49:22,960
Not at all.

722
00:49:23,040 --> 00:49:25,800
I've been counting down to the moment
I could see both of you.

723
00:49:25,880 --> 00:49:29,040
Sweetie, you're such a sweet talker.

724
00:49:29,640 --> 00:49:32,000
Come on, dear. Let's talk over there.

725
00:49:32,080 --> 00:49:34,680
Right. There's someone waiting for you.

726
00:49:43,640 --> 00:49:45,800
- Don't you miss Dao?
- It's none of your business.

727
00:49:45,880 --> 00:49:48,320
You can lie to anyone.

728
00:49:48,400 --> 00:49:49,600
But can you really

729
00:49:50,200 --> 00:49:51,960
lie to yourself?

730
00:49:52,040 --> 00:49:52,960
Hey!

731
00:49:53,480 --> 00:49:54,320
Don't hurt women.

732
00:49:54,400 --> 00:49:56,200
NEXT EPISODE

733
00:49:56,280 --> 00:49:59,680
Oh, it hurts. It really hurts!

734
00:50:00,800 --> 00:50:02,080
Fill it up, please.

735
00:50:10,720 --> 00:50:11,720
Petch.

736
00:50:25,160 --> 00:50:30,040
<i>I wish I knew if I ever crossed your mind</i>

737
00:50:31,200 --> 00:50:36,600
<i>I wish I knew if you heard the whisper</i>

738
00:50:37,120 --> 00:50:43,080
<i>For my heart is crying out my love</i>
<i>It's deep and true</i>

739
00:50:43,160 --> 00:50:48,320
<i>But never reaching you</i>

740
00:50:49,120 --> 00:50:53,880
<i>I know that it simply cannot be</i>

741
00:50:55,040 --> 00:50:59,640
<i>And I never want to cause you misery</i>

742
00:51:01,640 --> 00:51:06,880
<i>I'm just an ordinary man</i>
<i>Worth nothing at all</i>

743
00:51:07,480 --> 00:51:11,840
<i>And I never want to make</i>
<i>Your teardrops fall</i>

744
00:51:14,000 --> 00:51:18,480
<i>You are out of reach</i>

745
00:51:19,080 --> 00:51:23,880
<i>Is it a crime that I need you?</i>

746
00:51:26,160 --> 00:51:30,960
<i>Please let me know for sure</i>

747
00:51:31,040 --> 00:51:36,320
<i>That you're the one I've been waiting for</i>

748
00:51:37,160 --> 00:51:41,720
<i>How much longer can I bear this pain?</i>

749
00:51:43,200 --> 00:51:47,680
<i>How much longer must I wait in vain?</i>

750
00:51:49,240 --> 00:51:54,120
<i>I really don't know what move to make</i>

751
00:51:55,240 --> 00:52:00,200
<i>To end this heartache</i>
<i>And say that I love you</i>

752
00:52:00,280 --> 00:52:02,600
Subtitle translation by: Sarunpon T.
